The paper deals with the problem of efficiently streaming zoomable video to a set of heterogeneous users, which involves optimizing the transmission of independently decodable tiles to different users with different link rates and regions of interest. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including multimedia (cs.MM), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), and systems and control (cs.SY). Among these, cs.MM and cs.NI are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on multimedia streaming over wireless networks, which is a key research area in both fields.
